Questions:
What is the primary goal of the "Synbiotic Supplementation to Reduce Anxiety Symptoms in Female Breast Cancer Survivors" study?
A) To assess the impact of synbiotic supplements on physical fitness levels;
B) To investigate the effects of synbiotic supplements on anxiety symptoms in female breast cancer survivors;
C) To determine the effectiveness of synbiotic supplements in curing breast cancer;
D) To explore the relationship between synbiotic supplements and weight loss in women over 50.

Correct answer: B

Which of the following is considered the experimental procedure in the study "Synbiotic Supplementation to Reduce Anxiety Symptoms in Female Breast Cancer Survivors"?

A) Routine blood tests and physical measurements such as height and weight;
B) Administration of a daily synbiotic or placebo supplement over the course of the study;
C) Completion of anxiety symptom questionnaires and dietary assessments;
D) Collection and analysis of fecal samples to study the gut microbiome.

Correct answer: B

What alternative options are available to you if you choose not to participate in the "Synbiotic Supplementation to Reduce Anxiety Symptoms in Female Breast Cancer Survivors" study?
A) You will be required to participate in a different study focused on anxiety reduction;
B) You will be provided with a standard anxiety treatment by the research team;
C) You can choose not to participate without affecting your insurance coverage or healthcare delivery;
D) There are no alternative options available outside of the study.

Correct answer: C

If you experience any issues or have concerns about your rights as a participant in the "Synbiotic Supplementation to Reduce Anxiety Symptoms in Female Breast Cancer Survivors" study, whom should you contact?

A) The study coordinator or principal investigator;  
B) The nearest hospital emergency department;  
C) The Auburn University Office of Research Compliance/IRB;  
D) The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA).

Correct answer: C) The Auburn University Office of Research Compliance/IRB.
